  <body>
    <div style="basic">
        <p begin="00:00:00.000" end="00:00:04.040" tts:direction="ltr">Get multiple measures onto the view.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:04.040" end="00:00:06.280" tts:direction="ltr">What you'll need to do is,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:06.280" end="00:00:08.520" tts:direction="ltr">this is my example with Utah.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:08.520" end="00:00:11.400" tts:direction="ltr">I'm going to go ahead and drag a week up
<br />onto</p>
        <p begin="00:00:11.400" end="00:00:17.400" tts:direction="ltr">columns and I'm going to change that to a
<br />measure.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:17.400" end="00:00:21.200" tts:direction="ltr">I'm going to go for, let's go month for
<br />now.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:21.200" end="00:00:25.960" tts:direction="ltr">Now what I want to do is actually drag
<br />measure values.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:25.960" end="00:00:28.600" tts:direction="ltr">These two are created by Tableau.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:28.600" end="00:00:33.520" tts:direction="ltr">In fact, anything that's italicized is
<br />created by Tableau.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:33.520" end="00:00:36.800" tts:direction="ltr">In this case, because in the data source,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:36.800" end="00:00:38.680" tts:direction="ltr">I've connected, let me go back.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:38.680" end="00:00:42.840" tts:direction="ltr">I've connected all of my data together
<br />based on week.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:42.840" end="00:00:45.080" tts:direction="ltr">If I look at this connection really quick,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:45.080" end="00:00:47.480" tts:direction="ltr">you can see it's week to week.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:47.480" end="00:00:53.400" tts:direction="ltr">Then it creates this one where they're all
<br />connected.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:53.400" end="00:00:56.000" tts:direction="ltr">I'm going to drag measure values</p>
        <p begin="00:00:56.000" end="00:01:00.600" tts:direction="ltr">onto rows and you're going to see lots of
<br />stuff for now.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:00.600" end="00:01:07.800" tts:direction="ltr">But what I want to do is remove the ones
<br />that I don't want to have on there.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:07.800" end="00:01:11.440" tts:direction="ltr">I don't want to do the count of any of
<br />these.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:11.440" end="00:01:13.400" tts:direction="ltr">It does the count and the sum.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:13.400" end="00:01:15.780" tts:direction="ltr">I'm just going to drag those off.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:15.780" end="00:01:21.000" tts:direction="ltr">Now you can see I've got five of these
<br />different lines.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:21.000" end="00:01:24.880" tts:direction="ltr">But I need to change this again to an
<br />average.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:24.880" end="00:01:29.800" tts:direction="ltr">The sum does not reflect that zero to 100,</p>
        <p begin="00:01:29.800" end="00:01:37.360" tts:direction="ltr">so I need to change that to those
<br />averages. Here we go.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:38.560" end="00:01:41.280" tts:direction="ltr">Now that's better representing.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:41.280" end="00:01:43.360" tts:direction="ltr">Now I've got all four of them on there.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:43.360" end="00:01:47.000" tts:direction="ltr">Now I can go in here and let's see.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:47.000" end="00:01:51.920" tts:direction="ltr">Let's go ahead and add those measure
<br />names.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:52.000" end="00:01:56.920" tts:direction="ltr">Actually, not on to detail. Let me just
<br />take that off.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:56.920" end="00:02:00.880" tts:direction="ltr">Let me do measure values onto detail.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:00.880" end="00:02:04.360" tts:direction="ltr">I should be able to then color those.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:04.360" end="00:02:05.920" tts:direction="ltr">I'm not quite sure what's happening.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:05.920" end="00:02:07.800" tts:direction="ltr">Let me go back to do I</p>
        <p begin="00:02:07.800" end="00:02:14.640" tts:direction="ltr">make I put measure names on color, that
<br />should have worked.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:14.640" end="00:02:18.280" tts:direction="ltr">Let me just see. I don't know why that's
<br />going on to detail.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:18.280" end="00:02:21.440" tts:direction="ltr">There we go. Measure names on color.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:21.440" end="00:02:25.040" tts:direction="ltr">Measure values on rows or within</p>
        <p begin="00:02:25.040" end="00:02:28.680" tts:direction="ltr">here will allow you to create and put
<br />multiple on there.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:28.680" end="00:02:33.200" tts:direction="ltr">Measure names on color will allow you to
<br />have those three different colors.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:33.200" end="00:02:40.120" tts:direction="ltr">Remember to change the axes here to be
<br />zero to 100.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:40.120" end="00:02:41.640" tts:direction="ltr">You just right click that,</p>
        <p begin="00:02:41.640" end="00:02:48.120" tts:direction="ltr">edit axes and let's do that custom and
<br />change that to 100.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:48.720" end="00:02:56.520" tts:direction="ltr">There we go. Then, you can modify that
<br />accordingly.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:56.520" end="00:03:01.040" tts:direction="ltr">Hopefully that helps you Libby happy
<br />visiting.</p>
    </div>
  </body>
